Jennings had hoped to return to the anchor desk as his health and strength permitted. But he never did. He wrote later that he once decided to go to the office "I got as far as the door. Chemo strikes". He also received radiation. He never again appeared on air. Until his final days, he believed he could win his battle but he died on 7 August at his home in New York. He was 67. President Bush paid tribute. More than 25,000 viewers posted messages on the ABC News site. A two-hour memorial service was held at Carnegie Hall. 